The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Thursday, March 11, 2004 				 Party goes professional with focus on GeNext
 DEVADEEP PUROHIT																								Calcutta, March 10: The initiator of economic reforms in the country, preserver of Indias social fabric and promoter of young leaders  the Congress has chosen the key strengths on which the party will build its election campaign against the National Democratic Alliance led by Atal Bihari Vajpayee.																								To add professionalism to its election campaign, the Congress sealed a deal with Delhi-headquartered public relations agency Perfect Relations last month.																								The Congress young face as against the ageing leadership of the BJP will be focused on extensively. Twenty young leaders will criss-cross the country with the partys messages and we will manage their communications, Perfect Relations consulting partner Dilip Cherian said.																								Promoting the countrys oldest political partys young face in this election will hold the key, said Cherian. And to woo GeneratioNext, the Congress list of young leaders include Jyotiraditya Scindia (son of Madhav Rao Scindia), Sachin Pilot (son of Rajesh Pilot), Nadeem Javed, Alka Lamba, Manish Tiwari and Apok Jameer.																								While the industry is abuzz with rumours about the size of the contract running into crores, Cherian declined to comment on the financial side of the deal.																								Over 70 professionals from Perfect Relations, which had earlier managed the BJPs communication in the recently-held Assembly polls, will be working on the assignment. 																								The strategy is being worked out in consultation with the Congress media cell comprising Ambika Soni, Ahmed Patel, Jairam Ramesh and Salman Khursheed. It is being drawn up keeping in mind the Congress weaknesses, which include the BJPs success in hijacking the economic growth scenario and mobilising resources for the campaign. 
